# Azure DevOps Configuration
# The ADO MCP server uses OAuth (browser-based login) — no secrets needed here.
# You will be prompted to sign in with your Microsoft account on first use.

# Your ADO organization name (the part after dev.azure.com/ in your ADO URL)
# Example: if your ADO URL is https://dev.azure.com/contoso, the org name is "contoso"
ADO_ORGANIZATION=your-organization-name

# This value is set via VS Code MCP input prompt — no .env file is required.
# This file exists only as a reference for the organization name format.
